rComments: Lectures were basically her reading off of the slides, you could get away with skipping sometimes. Tutorials are helpful and provide good practice. The best thing you could do is keep practicing from the book and check out the old exams. Be prepared to get questions you've never seen before and know how to implement what you've learned.

This is one of the most caring professors at UTM! Consolidation is hard but Kathy makes it easy to understand and wants every student to understand material. She will explain in office hours or over email and truly cares about her students, also really nice and funny :)

She makes sure that you understand the materials. However, the midterm questions are really challenging and doing questions from the textbooks are not that really helpful. For winter 2017, her midterms are a bit easier than her midterms.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Kathy is nice and but what you do in class is  baby food compared to what you are tested on. So it can be deceiving! also don't rely on her posting anything later on portal just get all down in class , even the questions you do in class.
shes really funny and her lectures arent boring shes actually adorable but the course itself is a pain in the ass, keep up and youll do great but its so much knowledge i almost failed
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lots of homework', 'Hilarious']

rComments: MGT220 is super easy and Kathy is very very nice. However, Kathy knows how to fail a class by misguiding students on what is on the midterm/exam. (If she says this will be on the midterm/exam, it "might not" be there) She also throws in a couple of unique questions that students don't expect and never covered in class....
She was okay. The slides and lectures were not helpful for tests or exam. Read the textbook and do all the assigned h.w. questions. They need to get better T.A.s.

Great Professor! So helpful and really, really nice. Teaches everything clearly and makes accounting easy to understand! Final is harder than midterm because the second half material is harder--she follows the textbook. Ask and she'll help!

She's a pretty good prof, not that good but not that bad either. she has slides, assigns works, gives out past tests that if you do them all you'll be guaranteed to do well in her class. she gives you all the help you need in the class
Lecture is more or less the same as the textbook so coming to lecture is a bit useless. Midterm and final is a piece of cake. Overall learning experience 2.5/5
shes nice and all, but shes strict ! she definitely knows how to fail a class
Absolutely terrible prof. Makes the midterm too easy and kills you on the final exam.

Nice Prof. Straightforward materials, but it does take time to go through. If you make effort, you will finally pay off, or vice versa. Have to study hard to get a fair grade! Final is much harder than midterm!! BB is really helpful!
nice prof. very kind much better than that piece of .... bailey
Nice prof.. Kathy rocks all the way!
